      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "b0e1681e_ff67b9fa",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/main/comm/msgdata/UpdateReq.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 104,
      "message": "agreed, that should do it (though I don't think there's any mismatch on types).\n\nNote: for the undeployed case, there's nothing that can be done about it other than to log the undeploy failures.  (Other option would be to remove the PDP from the rotation, but I don't think we want to do that.  For that matter, the others would probably fail, too.)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-05-11 22:16:34.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "2eb6ec25_f91f01c5",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "b584c27a_296f9211",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/main/comm/msgdata/UpdateReq.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 104,
      "message": "Agree with the comments.\nAbout the \"undeploy failure\" case, if a policy fails to undeploy, should that be added to deployedPolicies list? similar to how the policies that failed to deploy are added to undeployedPolicies list.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4903,
        "name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "display_name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "email": "ajith.sreekumar@bell.ca",
        "username": "a.sreekumar"
      },
      "updated": "2021-05-12 10:35:38.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "b0e1681e_ff67b9fa",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "4889a469_269edde1",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/main/comm/msgdata/UpdateReq.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 104,
      "message": "at this point, I'm thinking they should be left off the list, so that PAP will try to undeploy them again when the next heartbeat comes in, thus it will retry at each heartbeat.  However, we could add them to the list so that no auto-retry occurs and leave it up to the PAP client to manually request an undeploy again.\n\nnot sure we want to spend a lot of time on this, as it seems very unlikely",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-05-12 12:13:56.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "b584c27a_296f9211",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
